			<h1>Parking</h1>

			<p>Parking at both Art Center campuses is free. Students should stop by the Pubic Programs office during the first week of the term to pick up a copy of the Student Guide, which outlines campus parking regulations.</p>

			<h2>South Campus students:</h2>
			<p>950 S. Raymond Avenue: There are parking lots available on the north and south sides of the building.<br/>
			   870 S. Raymond Avenue: There is a parking lot located on the south side of the building.<br/> 
			   1111 S. Arroyo Parkway: There are spaces available in the underground parking lot on the P1 level (only). Entrance to the lot is on Glenarm Street.</p>

			<p>During the first two weeks of classes, pick up your parking decal from Art Center Security at the information desk located at the first floor of South Campus, which is staffed from 7:00 a.m. to 10:00 p.m. Please bring your current course schedule, vehicle registration and license plate number.</p>

			<h2>Hillside Campus students:</h2>
			<p>1700 Lida Street: The student parking lot is located at the top of MacMinn Drive. Drop-offs on MacMinn Drive are strictly prohibited. If someone is dropping you off or picking you up, they must do so in the student parking lot.</p>
			
			<p>During the first two weeks of classes, please pick up your parking decal at the Hillside reception desk (located in the Student Gallery), which is staffed from 7:30 a.m. to 10:00 p.m. Please bring your current course schedule, vehicle registration and license plate number.</p>

			<h2>Students enrolled in short workshops (1-3 sessions):</h2>
			<p>Please print out a copy of your course schedule and place it on the dashboard of your vehicle.<p> 

			<h2>Parking tickets:</h2>
			<p>Parking tickets should be paid in person at the cashier’s window in the Hillside Campus’ Accounting office.</p>

			<p><span class="highlight">Cashier’s window:</span><br />
			626.396.2332<br />
			Hours: Mon., Tues., Thurs. and Fri.:  9 a.m.–1:15 p.m., 2:30–4 p.m.; Weds. 9 a.m. – 1:15 p.m.</p>

			<p>After you pay your parking fines, you will need to stop by or contact the Enrollment Services office to have the parking restriction removed from your school records.</p>

			<p><span class="highlight">Enrollment Services:</span><br />
			626.396.2314<br />
			Hours: Monday through Friday, 8:30 a.m.–4:30 p.m.</p>

			<p>You have until the end of the term to pay parking fines, however you will not be able to register for the subsequent term or receive your grades until you have cleared up any restrictions.</p>		

